      <hedline>
        <hl1>DONATING FOR AFRICA</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Augustus Nasmith Jr letter on recent travel articles about Ethiopia, Kenya, Zambia and Zimbabwe suggests that travelers make small donations to local African charitable organizations and make purchases at grassroots markets and craft cooperatives</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Your positive articles about Ethiopia, Kenya, Zambia and Zimbabwe didn't need to so ignore the plights of their people and the huge toll of H.I.V./AIDS. What about suggesting a sort of ''Robin Hood'' donation -- a small percentage of the amount it would cost a first-world traveler to visit Africa -- to local charitable organizations? In addition, direct purchases in grassroots markets and craft cooperatives are not only fun and provide wonderful gifts, but they also support large extended families in need.</p>
        <p>Augustus Nasmith, Jr.  Rutland, Vt.</p>
      </block>
